                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-14T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Your telegram March 13, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>Argentine Government has not yet made any decision in the matter. Neither Western
                    Telegraph Company nor British Legation is pushing matter, nor does either appear
                    to take much interest therein. Does Department desire Embassy to endeavor to
                    hasten matter?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Riddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
